title: For Sale:  CERAKOTE! Hard, bake-on, ceramic finish for just about everything!
postcontent:
We provide coating services for all types of metal, polymer and plastic products. We can coat anything from firearms and knives, to industrial and automotive parts. If you want it coated, we can coat it. Testing Performed by an independent military approved testing facility proved that Cerakote™ is 7.5 times more wear resistant than other coatings including, but not limited to, duracoat, gunkote, parkerizing, powder coating, blueing, ion bond, etc. You can coat your items in virtually any color you want.

We also offer Micro Slick services. Cerakote™ Micro Slick is a dry-film lubricant that is able to withstand high temperatures and extreme pressures. The Micro Slick coating is able to lubricate, resist wear, and also act as an anti-seize agent while preventing galvanic corrosion or bonding of the metals. Micro Slick is virtually unaffected by temperatures ranging between 800 and 12000 degrees fahrenheit. When two adjoining surfaces are coated with Micro Slick it prevents surface-to-surface contact, which reduces friction and wear between the two surfaces. An example of this would be to coat a bolt carrier group on an AR 15 and the inside of the upper receiver. This combination would reduce the amount of friction between the parts and help the firearm to function more smoothly.

Micro Slick is generally applied, but not limited, to internal, moving parts such as bolts, bolt carrier groups, trigger groups, rails, etc. This product comes in a dark grey color only.

title: For Sale:  Burris 3-9X-40 Fullfield II Ballistic Plex Riflescope AND 10X-32mm Landmark Binocular
postcontent:
BRAND NEW in factory sealed package. Scope by itself retails for $200, so you're basically getting the binoculars for free (which retail for $115). Willing to ship for $15.00 extra.

Burris 3-9x40mm Fullfield II Rifle Scope w/ Burris 10x32mm Landmark Binoculars gives you a full spot-and-shoot package! This value package from Burris includes the Burris 3x-9x 40mm Fullfield-II Riflescope and the Burris Landmark 10x32mm Binoculars.

The Burris Fullfield II Rifle Scope has a one-piece main tube and eyepiece, Burris envied steel-on-steel adjustment system, and HiLume multi-coatings on every single air to glass lens surface. The Burris FullField-II Scope is even more forgiving for eye position, is a little shorter, and a good bit lighter. The magnification ring and eyepiece have been made into one solid unit requiring only two seals rather than three. To change magnification, simply turn the entire eyepiece. Burris Fullfield 2 Scope eliminated most of the potential leak paths in the eyepiece/power ring area and sealed the remainder with special quad seals instead of O-rings. The adjustment system has been moved to improve mounting options and the European-style adjustable eyepiece requires no locking mechanism. The Ballistic Plex reticle has a lower vertical crosshair with small ballistic lines that automatically compensate for bullet drop from 100 to 500 yards for many common cartridges. The Burris Fullfield-2 Riflescope is lighter, better sealed, and has a relocated adjustment system compared to the original Burris Fullfield.

The Burris Landmark Binoculars combine light weight, fully coated lenses and water resistant, fogproof construction. These Burris Binoculars also include a tough rubber armor coating and twist-up eyecups. Top all this off with a neck strap, carrying case, a full year warranty and a very affordable price and you have yourself a synonym for optical value.

Specifications for Burris 3-9x40 Fullfield II Rifle Scope:
Tube Diameter: 1"
Objective (front) Diameter: 48mm
Ocular (rear) Diameter: 39mm
Adjustable Objective: No

Features of Burris 3-9x40mm Fullfield II Rifle Scope:

Waterproof: All Burris optics are proven to be absolutely waterproof. Each scope is submerged in water with a temperature of 50° C. The extremely hot water transfers its heat to the scope and the internal nitrogen expends 100% testing assures quality. Each scope is filled and purged at least 24 times with high quality, laboratory grade dry nitrogen. Each nitrogen cycle absorbs airborne and residual surface moisture that is evacuated from the scope. Burris uses specially made quad seals to provide double insurance against leakage.
Fog proof: The nitrogen contained in the scope is of high quality (ultra dry, laboratory grade nitrogen), ultra pure and ultra clean. To be sure that all airborne moisture and surfaces moisture within a scope is evacuated, testing consists of 24 cycles of pressurizing the scope and then subjecting it to a vacuum. The tests are both cost & time intensive.
Shock proof: Burris scopes are subjected to extreme recoil tests. An impact machine is used to measure and duplicate the recoil pulse acceleration and duration. This machine has been calibrated and verified by an independent laboratory to replicate the wave frequencies and shock impulses that a scope is subjected to.
Ballistic Plex reticle - with a basic crosshair reticle, calculating hold-over is a mix of art, science and just plain luck, which is why Burris developed the Ballistic Plex reticle. The key is the copyrighted lower vertical crosshair. With most common hunting cartridges, a shooter can use the reticle to compensate for bullet drop and aim dead-on at targets from 100 to 500 yards out. The need for hold-over guesstimation is eliminated. Using it is simple. Start by sighting-in your rifle at 100 or 200 yards at your scope's highest magnification. Then, once you determine the distance to your target, select the appropriate ballistic line. Add slight hold-over or hold-under for in-between yardages and take the shot.
Includes binoculars!

title: For Sale:  Colt 1911 Pre-WW2 / National Match "Type 3" Full-Checkered Walnut Grips
postcontent:
Colt 1911 Wood Grips, Full Checkering, Walnut. These replaced the earlier WW-1 era Type-1 Walnut "Double Diamond" Grips, and the rare 1918 Type-2 Bakelite Varient.  These were used from the late 20's until 1941 on Full Size Colt M1911's, and M1911A1's until approximately S/N 730,000, when they were replaced by the Type-4 plastic grips used on USGI pistols until they were phased out with the introduction of the Beretta M9 pistol in the late 1980's.  These Type-3 Walnut Grips were also used after WW2 on National Match pistols by the U.S. Army Marksmanship Unit (my father was a member of the USAMU and I acquired these from his estate.)  They are excellent overall. There is a little dirt in the diamonds. I didn't clean or change. I am selling "as is."  $5.50 to ship in a well packed Priority Mail box. Any M4 MIL Std 1913 accessory can be mounted to the rail, and because the rail has a monolithic profile, you can bridge devices from the receiver to the rail seamlessly. All M6A2™ rifles feature a match grade, cold rotary hammer forged barrel with a target crown. The barrel is treated with NiCorr™ surface conversion technology that extends service life, enhances accuracy, and increases the effective range of the weapon. As in all of our rifles, the bolt carrier group and the barrel extension of the M6A2™ rifle is coated with EXO’s patented nickel-boron surface conversion technology that provides a hard permanent lubrication to the moving parts.

The M6A2™ rifle defines itself as the most modern and incrementally evolved carbine in the world. At the same time it also presents the best value. title: For Sale:  Rifles for sale, ammo, dies, brass, reloading equipment.
postcontent:
I have 4 firearms that I'm trying to sell. We are forced with financial hardship to let loose of some material possessions. I have an interarms 30-06 with a pretty decent scope, it is a tasco and was 159.99 new. The firearm itself was manufactured in alexandria, va and is modeled after the mauser. The bolt assembly itself is listed online for $250 because it can go right onto a mauser. I value the gun at around $400 without all of the extras for it, such as 20 rounds of ammo, reloading dies with extra depriming pins, 160 rounds of brass (100 of which are polished and deprimed), and case trimming length gauge, along with 2 shell holders. I would let it go for $350 alone and $420 with the extras. The 30-06 is the one on the bottom.

Also for sale is a remington 550-1 semi-auto tube fed 22lr, 22short, 22long. I have one box of 49 rounds of subsonic CCI CB22 short ammo and 25 rounds of remington hyper velocity 22 short golden rounds that I will include."These older Remingtons are super shooters. They have REAL walnut stocks and all steel parts. Except for the buttplate, you won't see any plastic or potmetal on them." There is not a semi-auto 22 rifle made these days that can use a 22 short and work the extractor. In 90% condition they are worth $350 all day long. This gun is not in that condition, in fact it is currently disassembled and the barrel is stripped to bare steel because I'm in the process of blueing it. I would sell it right now how it sits for $150 (I would reassemble it of course, so you can see that it operates properly before buying). After I blue it and take the paint rub off of the stock I will be selling it at $300 price tag. This is the second gun from the bottom  in the picture. I just slapped the barrel on the stock, it also has a weaver side mount scope for it so you can have your iron sights and scope both with easy visibilty.

3rd from the bottom is a marlin model 60 22lr semi-auto tube fed 15+1. This gun is $200 new and have a $30 tasco scope that you see in the pictures with the ammo. It also has high visibility fiber optics iron sights which I have used at night and work well. I am also selling this for $150. I am not including the 50 ($5) rounds of CCI minimags, the 525($24.99) rounds of remington golden rounds, or the federal ($20) high velocity 22lr rounds in the deal but would be willing to sell this ammo separate for $30.

Finally at the top of the picture is the H & R Pardner pump 12g shotgun. This is a 5+1 pump action that is modeled after the Remington Express 870, I have a shoulder sling that I paid $30 for that is on it in the picture. We paid just over $200 new for this gun, this gun is just about brand new was bought as a Christmas gift, has only had 30 rounds put through it. All of the shotgun ammo in the picture comes with it. 2 boxes (50 rounds)of winchester target ammo, 1 box of remington #4 shot pheasant load, 4 boxes of federal #7 1/2 shot multi-purpose rounds. 5 rounds of winchester security ammo, has slug with 3 pellets of 00 buckshot. 10 remington rifled slug rounds and 5 rounds 00 buckshot. This is about $80 worth of ammunition. So I value it all about about $310 and will sell it for $230.

I also have a Lyman eazy-loader 3 stage reloading press($199), an electronic micrometer($30), 2 ammo cans ($35), one wooden 100 round casing holder($15). Bottle of birchwood casey Brass cleaning solution($10) and an RCBS gun powder scale($169). The steel box in the background is the case for the press. This is easily $400 worth of stuff, but I will let it go for $150, because of our current need.

By my math you could get everything here at my discounted price for $1130, if you were to come and take all off my hands I would come down to $1000. This is an insane deal and I would also throw in all of my gun cleaning accessories as well, around $75 worth of stuff if one were to take all. 

Within the first 48 hours I will not be responding to any replies to break up the collection as I'm wanting to give a chance for someone to take it all. After that if there is no one who will take it all, than I will start going down the list of the emails I received first.

I've got more pictures and/or can take more if you need, just let me know. Am willing to ship through an FFL if you were to pay all the fees.

Quotes regarding remington 22 cited http://www.go2gbo.com/forums/index.php?topic=51593.0
